I beg to move Amendment No. 1181, in page 218, leave out lines 49 to 55 and insert:
'the borough of Bangor;
the urban district of Bethesda;
the rural district of Ogwen.
GD 3 A, In the administrative county of Caernarvon;
the borough of Caernarvon;
the rural district of Gwyrfai except the parts to be comprised in G.D.2'.
The purpose of the Amendment is to divide the proposed District 3 of the new County of Gwynedd into two separate districts, one based on the Royal Borough of Carnaervon and the other on the Cathedral City of Bangor. My right hon. and learned Friend the Secretary of State not only knows all the arguments involved in this case; he also knows the area. He has written to the mayor of Bangor and the Chairmen of the Bethesda and Ogwen councils.

I am sorry that at this late stage I am not able to put the full case to the House, but I know that my right hon. and learned Friend is well aware of it, and I ask him to comment.
